@startuml fuel_battery_to_isg_restart_ready_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Fuel Battery To ISG Restart Ready Signal Flow\n(fuel-battery + vehicle mode/state -> ISG restart-ready publication)

participant "Fuel/Battery source\nBatterySoc / ChargingState" as FB #E8F0FE
participant "VCU\nvehicle-mode producer" as VCU #E8F7E8
participant "Vehicle state\nDriveState / VehicleSpeed" as Veh #F4F7FB
participant "ISG\nidle-stop-go owner" as ISG #FFF4CC
participant "Powertrain observers" as Obs #FCE8FF

== ISG Inputs ==

FB -> ISG : frmFuelBatteryStateMsg\nBatterySoc / ChargingState
VCU -> ISG : frmVehicleModeMsg\nDriveMode / PowertrainState
Veh -> ISG : frmVehicleStateCanMsg\nDriveState / VehicleSpeed
activate ISG
ISG -> ISG : normalize stale fuel-battery / vehicle inputs
ISG -> ISG : derive IsgState from PowertrainState,\nBatterySoc, DriveState, VehicleSpeed
ISG -> ISG : derive RestartReady / RecuperationLvl
note right of ISG
Representative outputs
- IsgState
- RestartReady
- RecuperationLvl
end note

== ISG Publish ==

ISG -> Obs : frmIsgStateMsg
ISG -> Obs : traceable restart-ready / regen state
deactivate ISG

note over FB, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Fuel-battery state reaches ISG with vehicle mode/state context
2. ISG derives idle-stop-go state and restart readiness
3. Recuperation level is adjusted from speed and charging context
4. Powertrain observers verify restart and regen behavior
end note

@enduml
